{{Infobox organization | name = International Vegetarian Union | logo = IVU logo.png | logo_size = 220px | type = | founded_date = 1908 | founder = | location = United Kingdom | origins = | key_people = John Davis, manager, webmaster | area_served = World | product = | mission = | focus = Vegetarianism | method = | revenue = | endowment = | num_volunteers = | num_employees = | num_members = | subsid = | owner = | Non-profit_slogan = Promoting Vegetarianism Worldwide Since 1908 | homepage = [http://www.ivu.org/ www.ivu.org] | dissolved = | footnotes = }}
The '''International Vegetarian Union''' ('''IVU''') is an international non-profit [[Non-governmental organization|organization]] whose purpose is to promote vegetarianism. IVU was founded in 1908 in [[Dresden]], Germany.<ref>[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/624623/vegetarianism/258891/The-17th-through-19th-centuries#ref=ref828014 Vegetarianism The 17th through 19th centuries] [[Encyclopædia Britannica]]</ref><ref>[http://www.ivu.org/congress/wvc08/germany-de.html IVU Welt-Vegetarier-Kongress 1908] IVU (German)</ref>
It is considered as an [[umbrella organization]] for under this organisation are included organisations from many countries,<ref>[http://www.vilaweb.cat/www/noticia?p_idcmp=1594564 Dia mundial dels veganisme] 01/11/2005 [[Vilaweb]] {{ca icon}}</ref> and organises often World and Regional Vegetarian Congresses.<ref>[http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/ad13a7dc-312c-11d9-a595-00000e2511c8.html Monday 8 UK] 8 November 2004 [[Financial Times]]</ref> These alternate in two-year cycles.
==Description== The ruling body from IVU is the International Council, and the members who form it are unpaid volunteers elected by the Member Societies at each World Vegetarian Congress.
Member organizations may be continental groups (EVU, VUNA,<ref>[http://www.IVU.org/vuna/ VUNA]</ref> [[NAVS]],<ref>[http://www.NAVS-Online.org NAVS]</ref> etc.) or local or other regional vegetarian organizations whose primary purpose is the promotion of vegetarianism and the support of vegetarian living (e.g. EarthSave<ref>[http://www.EarthSave.org EarthSave]</ref>).
The IVU also encourages regional and national organizations to run vegetarian festivals, such as the 43rd WorldVegFest in [[Sydney]] and [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]], on 25 October 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldvegfest.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=367:ivu-world-vegfest-in-australia&catid=21&Itemid=293|title=IVU World Vegfest in Australia|date=19 May 2015|publisher=IVU World VegFest|accessdate=23 September 2015}}</ref>
== Notable members== * [[Gordon Latto (doctor)]]
==Regional groups== * Asian Pacific Vegetarian Union (APVU) * [[European Vegetarian Union]] (founded in 1988) * Vegetarian Union of North America (preceded by the American Vegetarian Union 1949–1970s and the North American Vegetarian Society 1974–1987<ref>[https://ivu.org/history/societies/americanvu.html The American Vegetarian Union]</ref>) * South American Vegetarian Union * Southeast Asian Vegetarian Union
