'''Kalyan Mal Lodha''' is an educationist, [[Hindi]] writer, literary critic and social reformer{{cn|date=May 2017}} who served as vice-chancellor of [[Jodhpur University]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Padatik felicitates Usha Ganguly |work=Daily Excelsior |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070619090230/http://www.dailyexcelsior.com/99nov14/national.htm |archivedate=2007-06-19 |url=http://www.dailyexcelsior.com/99nov14/national.htm}}</ref>

Lodha was born in [[Jodhpur]], [[Rajasthan]], and now lives in [[Kolkata]]. He has contributed significantly to the cause of [[Jain]] religion and Jain community.{{cn|date=May 2017}} He was Head of the Department of Hindi at [[Calcutta University]].{{cn|date=May 2017}}

Lodha was presented with the [[Bihari Award]] by [[K. K. Birla Foundation]] at Kolkata for his book titled ''Vagdwar''. It comprises a thorough study of the productions of eight prominent Hindi poets, Tulsi, Soordas, Kabir, Nirala, [[Maithili Sharan Gupta]], Jai Shankar Prasad, [[Mahadevi Verma]] and Makhanlal Chaturvedi.{{cn|date=May 2017}}

