{{Original research|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox ethnic group |group= Vannar/Rajaka/Suriyakulam |regions = {{flag|India}} {{center|{{small|Other significant population centers:}}}} {{hlist|{{flag|Sri Lanka}}}} |population = 20,72,625 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vikatan.com/vc/2009/pelect/subpage.asp?artid=1482|title=Tamil News - Latest Tamil News - Tamil News Online - Vikatan|website=Vikatan|accessdate=7 October 2017}}</ref> | langs ={{hlist|[[Tamil language|Tamil]] | [[Telugu language|Telugu]]}} | rels ={{hlist|[[Hindu]] | [[Muslim]] | [[Christian]]}} | related ={{hlist|[[Dhobi]] | [[Rajaka]]}} }}
The '''Vannar''' ({{lang-ta|வண்ணார்}}) caste is primarily in the Indian state of [[Tamil Nadu]] and [[Sri Lanka]]. They are an washerman caste, classified as [[Other Backward Class|Most Backward Class]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.tehelka.com/story_main13.asp?filename=Cr082705Caught_in_the.asp |title=Tehelka - The People's Paper |publisher=Archive.tehelka.com |date=2005-08-27 |accessdate=2016-05-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141211045717/http://archive.tehelka.com/story_main13.asp?filename=Cr082705Caught_in_the.asp |archive-date=2014-12-11 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
== History == In the [[Tamil Nadu]] state of India, the Vannar's form 4 or 5%{{Citation needed|date=November 2016}} of the total population and they are considered Most backward caste. Their nature of business is laundry and agriculture. Their social status need help and the community is requesting Tamil Nadu Government to move them into Schedule caste and Government promised them to move them into Schedule caste over and over again but ignoring them from long time. The primary reason for this is from this community there is no representation in any higher positions in politics, nor any sort of government representation. <ref>http://keetru.com/index.php/2010-06-24-04-31-11/ungal-noolagam-oct16/31697-2016-10-21-02-30-43</ref>
